WEBVTT

NOTE Episode: The Bridge

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.830
<v Old Timber>Welcome... to another episode of Shiloh Creek....Where the water runs slow, the friends look out for each other, and every story starts here — pondside — with me.</v>

2
00:00:11.180 --> 00:00:24.860
<v Old Timber>I'm Old Timber....The elephant elder....And today's story... is the morning a bear-cub tried to lift a whole log...by himself....And what the friends learned... when they finally lifted it together.</v>

3
00:00:25.210 --> 00:00:40.130
<v Old Timber>Today... I want to ask you something, my friends....Have you ever tried to do a big thing...all by yourself?...When somebody was right next to you...who could have helped?...What does it mean...to ask first?...Even before you start lifting?...Listen carefully....The answer is in the story.</v>

4
00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:54.280
<v Old Timber>And here is one thing for you to know... before we start....God made each of us,...with different sizes...and different hands...and different gifts....And there is a reason....And today's story...is how the friends found that reason out.</v>

5
00:00:54.630 --> 00:00:58.485
<v Old Timber>Now... gather round. Come close by the pond.</v>

6
00:00:58.835 --> 00:01:05.635
<v Bongo>[excited]...Old Timber!...Is this the BRIDGE one?...The one where the LOG goes across the water?</v>

7
00:01:05.985 --> 00:01:11.385
<v Old Timber>Mm....Yes, Bongo....It is the bridge one....And the log one....Settle in.</v>

8
00:01:11.735 --> 00:01:14.235
<v Old Timber>Now... settle in....Here we go.</v>

9
00:01:25.765 --> 00:01:42.965
<v Old Timber>Now, this was a bright clear morning,...the kind that comes after a long night of rustly wind,...where everything looks washed and the leaves shine,...and the path is sprinkled with little twigs the breeze knocked down...and didn't bother to clean up.</v>

10
00:01:43.315 --> 00:02:00.115
<v Old Timber>And the friends had been planning,...for that very morning,...to walk together down to the berry patch on the south side....A small walk....A small bag for each pocket....Maybe a sit-down on the flat stone....Maybe a contest or two,...with Zippy keeping score.</v>

11
00:02:00.465 --> 00:02:14.265
<v Old Timber>But to GET to the berry patch on the south side,...the friends had to cross the creek....And to cross the creek,...they had to take the wooden footbridge....And the wooden footbridge that morning,...was — as it turned out — not exactly available.</v>

12
00:02:14.615 --> 00:02:18.415
<v Shelly>...Mm.....That'd be the log.</v>

13
00:02:18.765 --> 00:02:36.265
<v Old Timber>Because the wind in the night...had brought down a long old log...from the leaning maple on the bank....And the long old log...had landed right across...the middle of the footbridge....And it was lying there in the morning sun,...looking dignified...and immovable...and not at all sorry.</v>

14
00:02:36.615 --> 00:02:39.625
<v Old Timber>Now, this is where things got interesting...</v>

15
00:02:39.975 --> 00:02:54.175
<v Old Timber>And the first one down to the bridge that morning,...bouncing on his big paws like he'd been waiting all week,...was Bongo the bear cub....And he saw the log,...and his eyes got wide,...and he looked at it the way you look at a job...you have decided is YOURS....and he said,</v>

16
00:02:54.525 --> 00:03:09.125
<v Bongo>[excited]...I got this!...Friends — wherever you are —...DON'T WORRY....The bridge....The bridge has a log....And I — I am a BEAR....And bears...are LITERALLY...for lifting logs.</v>

17
00:03:09.475 --> 00:03:21.875
<v Old Timber>And just behind him —...because by now the friends had heard him,...and were arriving from across the meadow —...darted Zippy the hummingbird,...wings buzzing the morning awake,...and she said,</v>

18
00:03:22.225 --> 00:03:41.425
<v Zippy>Okay — okay — friends — I have done the SCAN — log is approximately one-point-eight metres long — diameter approximately twenty centimetres — estimated weight, given moisture content from last night's wind — between THIRTY and FORTY-TWO kilograms — Bongo, friend, that is a TWO-bear-cub job — possibly a two-bear-cub-and-one-elephant job —</v>

19
00:03:41.775 --> 00:03:51.575
<v Bongo>[excited]...Zippy....Zippy, friend....I appreciate the MATH....But the math is for OTHER bears....I am — I am THIS bear....I got this!</v>

20
00:03:51.925 --> 00:04:07.325
<v Old Timber>And from up high in the leaning maple — which had, after all, just delivered the log — came Garingo the parrot,...with feathers slightly ruffled from the breeze the maple still remembered,...and he called down — from beneath a leaf he had selected for resonance —</v>

21
00:04:07.675 --> 00:04:22.275
<v Garingo>BEHOLD!...The OBSTACLE!...A log,...long and stately,...having LEFT the maple it once was part of,...has chosen, this morning,...to LIE...directly across the footbridge....And Bongo the bear cub,...young and STRONG,...intends to address it...SINGLE-HANDEDLY.</v>

22
00:04:22.625 --> 00:04:35.425
<v Old Timber>And at the edge of the path —...slow as ever,...with morning light catching on her shell —...arrived Shelly the tortoise....She looked at the log....She looked at Bongo....She looked at the log again....And she said,</v>

23
00:04:35.775 --> 00:04:41.375
<v Shelly>...Bongo.....That log...is bigger than you.</v>

24
00:04:41.725 --> 00:04:50.325
<v Bongo>[excited]...Shelly....I — I know the log is bigger than me....It's just — it's not bigger than my HEART.</v>

25
00:04:50.675 --> 00:05:03.075
<v Old Timber>And then,...with the soft sound of small hooves...on dry path,...came Fern the fawn,...quiet and present,...wearing the morning easily on her back....And she came up beside the log...and looked at it...and looked at Bongo...and said,</v>

26
00:05:03.425 --> 00:05:12.625
<v Fern>...Bongo....I could push...from the back....If you wanted....I'm — I'm not very heavy....But I am pretty steady.</v>

27
00:05:12.975 --> 00:05:21.375
<v Bongo>[excited]...Fern....Fern, friend....I appreciate the OFFER....But I — I really do...got...this.</v>

28
00:05:21.725 --> 00:05:36.525
<v Old Timber>And then,...from the wet end of the path...just past the bridge —...arrived the Mudpuppy brothers — Splish, Splash, and Splosh —...three frogs, four feet of bridge between them and the friends,...wearing the morning's wet on their shoulders like a uniform....And Splish started,</v>

29
00:05:36.875 --> 00:05:43.075
<v Splish>I HAVE A FACT!...wait no, I have a QUESTION....Why...is the log...on the BRIDGE?</v>

30
00:05:43.425 --> 00:05:53.225
<v Splash>AND ALSO — !...The log...is BIG.....And the BRIDGE...is small.....The log,...if you ASK ME,...is OVER-QUALIFIED for being on a bridge.</v>

31
00:05:53.575 --> 00:06:02.975
<v Splosh>...Like a BELL.....On a COLD ROCK....BIG things, friends,...are like a BELL....On a COLD ROCK.</v>

32
00:06:03.325 --> 00:06:13.725
<v Bongo>[excited]...Friends....I love the THINKING....But I am LIFTING NOW....Watch this....Watch...this....I — am — going — to — lift — the LOG.</v>

33
00:06:14.075 --> 00:06:27.875
<v Old Timber>And so Bongo the bear cub,...with his whole heart in it,...braced his back paws on the wooden bridge planks,...wrapped his arms around the middle of the long old log,...took the kind of breath...a bear takes...when he means it,...and LIFTED.</v>

34
00:06:28.225 --> 00:06:47.425
<v Old Timber>And the log...moved...about four inches....And then,...because four inches is not enough for a log to do anything useful with,...the log...settled back down....And one end of it,...the heavier end,...slid sideways...and landed,...gently,...exactly...on Bongo's back paw.</v>

35
00:06:47.775 --> 00:07:01.575
<v Bongo>[excited]...Oh.....Oh, friends.....The log....The log is on my PAW....The log is on my PAW, friends....And I'm — I'm fine, I think,...but — the log is — the log is just — RIGHT THERE.</v>

36
00:07:01.925 --> 00:07:13.125
<v Old Timber>Now....The friends were all standing on the bridge....And the Mudpuppies were standing on the other side....And the log was on Bongo's paw....And Bongo's paw was not, just at the moment,...going anywhere.</v>

37
00:07:13.475 --> 00:07:29.875
<v Bongo>[excited]...Friends.....I'm — I'm going to say something.....I wanted to do this....By myself....I wanted you to walk up...and see the log gone....And know that I did it....I really wanted that.....And I — I think...I think I wanted it so much...that I didn't HEAR you.</v>

38
00:07:30.225 --> 00:07:44.825
<v Zippy>[excited]...Bongo....I — I — I had the numbers, friend....I said the numbers.....And I think....I think I said the numbers WITH the buzz on...so loud...that the numbers couldn't be heard....I — I might have said the answer in a way that was hard to hear.</v>

39
00:07:45.175 --> 00:07:54.775
<v Fern>...I didn't ask twice.....I offered once....And when you said no...I just....stopped.....I could have said it again.</v>

40
00:07:55.125 --> 00:08:06.925
<v Shelly>...Mm.....I said the log was bigger than you....I didn't say...I would help you with it.....I made the observation....I didn't make the offer.</v>

41
00:08:07.275 --> 00:08:19.875
<v Old Timber>Mm.....Yes....Of course you all did, my friends.....Each of you saw a piece....And nobody...put the pieces together....It happens.....More than you'd think.</v>

42
00:08:20.225 --> 00:08:27.025
<v Old Timber>Bongo....What did you not ask...before you lifted?</v>

43
00:08:27.375 --> 00:08:46.975
<v Bongo>[excited]...Old Timber.....I — I didn't ask...if you wanted to help....I didn't ask...what you needed me to do....I didn't ask...who could do which part.....I just — I just said I HAD it....And then I didn't....And I think....I think...God doesn't make us all the same size...for nothing.</v>

44
00:08:47.325 --> 00:08:48.525
<v Old Timber>Mm.</v>

45
00:08:48.875 --> 00:09:01.475
<v Old Timber>And there's a small book,...by an old king named Solomon,...that I have been thinking of all morning....A short line in it....About what happens...when friends do the work...together.....I'll come back to that line later.....For now....I think the friends...have a log to lift.</v>

46
00:09:01.825 --> 00:09:07.025
<v Bongo>[excited]...Friends....I'm — I'm going to ask now....What do you need me to do?</v>

47
00:09:07.375 --> 00:09:26.775
<v Zippy>[excited]...Okay....Friends — okay....Bongo — you brace UNDER the heavy end — that's your shoulder against the log low — Fern, you push from BEHIND on the lighter end — Shelly, you stand on the bridge side so when the log comes free you can call OFF — and Garingo — Garingo, can you keep an EYE on the leaning maple in case anything else decides to come down — and Mudpuppies — Mudpuppies, friends, can you call READY from your side so we know the bridge is clear —</v>

48
00:09:27.125 --> 00:09:37.325
<v Garingo>...EYE on the maple,...DULY accepted....I — I shall narrate any further developments,...should the tree...have ADDITIONAL opinions.</v>

49
00:09:37.675 --> 00:09:43.075
<v Fern>...I'll push from behind....I — I'll dig my hooves in....Just say when.</v>

50
00:09:43.425 --> 00:09:48.225
<v Shelly>...Mm.....Bridge side.....I'll call off.</v>

51
00:09:48.575 --> 00:09:58.375
<v Splosh>...READY,...friends.....READY on this side.....The BRIDGE...from our angle...has NO log on it.....The OTHER side...has all the log.</v>

52
00:09:58.725 --> 00:10:06.125
<v Splish>READY...also....I have a FACT....wait no — I have a QUESTION....Is...the bear...heavy enough to be the LIFTING end?</v>

53
00:10:06.475 --> 00:10:14.075
<v Splash>AND ALSO — !...The bear...IS HEAVY enough....I have CHECKED....I checked...with my EYES.</v>

54
00:10:14.425 --> 00:10:25.825
<v Old Timber>And so —...with everyone ready...and everyone knowing what their part was...and nobody trying to do anything by themselves —...the friends LIFTED.</v>

55
00:10:26.175 --> 00:10:48.975
<v Old Timber>And the long old log,...the one that had been so dignified and immovable five minutes earlier,...came UP off the bridge planks,...came OVER to the bank,...and came DOWN, quietly, in the soft earth beside the leaning maple it had once been part of....And the bridge was free....And the path to the south side was open.....And it had taken, by the morning's count,...about a minute.</v>

56
00:10:49.325 --> 00:11:03.525
<v Bongo>[excited]...Friends.....I want to say something....And I am going to say it...slowly.....I think...the friends...are how you lift the log....I think...when you ASK,...the answer...is BIGGER than you.....I — I think that's a thing.</v>

57
00:11:03.875 --> 00:11:08.235
<v Fern>...Bongo.....That's....exactly the thing.</v>

58
00:11:08.585 --> 00:11:15.385
<v Shelly>...Mm.....A small log, lifted together....A whole morning, recovered.</v>

59
00:11:15.735 --> 00:11:41.335
<v Old Timber>Mm.....And so the friends crossed the footbridge,...slow on the wood,...with Bongo helping Fern step over a wet patch,...and Garingo riding on Bongo's shoulder,...and Zippy ahead checking the planks,...and Shelly bringing up the rear,...and the Mudpuppies receiving the friends on the wet side with three small splash-bows....And we walked together,...down to the berry patch on the south side....And the morning,...as it turned out,...had quite a lot in it.</v>

60
00:11:41.685 --> 00:12:01.285
<v Old Timber>Now....After all of that —...once the berries had been picked,...and a small pile had been made on the flat stone,...and Zippy had scored a contest that nobody was technically having —...we sat together under the big old oak,...where the leaves go thickest,...and looked back at the bridge,...and the footbridge,...and the spot on the bank where the long old log was now lying quietly...beside the leaning maple it had come from.</v>

61
00:12:01.635 --> 00:12:07.235
<v Old Timber>And I asked them — friends, what do you think it was, in the end,...that made the morning work?</v>

62
00:12:07.585 --> 00:12:19.385
<v Bongo>[excited]...I think.....I think it was when I ASKED.....Instead of just LIFTING.....And when I asked,...the friends were already there....They were just...waiting for me to ASK.</v>

63
00:12:19.735 --> 00:12:29.135
<v Fern>...I think....it was that everybody had a part....And the parts...were different sizes....And that was the POINT.</v>

64
00:12:29.485 --> 00:12:43.285
<v Zippy>[excited]...I think....it was the algorithm....The team-shape algorithm.....It works better when everybody runs the same one.....Including me.....I — I sometimes run my own.....I think that's the FIX.</v>

65
00:12:43.635 --> 00:12:56.835
<v Garingo>...I think.....it was that the LOG....which I had ANNOUNCED to be...immovable,...and dignified,...and not at all sorry —...turned out to be...lift-able...by six.....The LOG,...as it turned out,...had been WAITING for SIX.</v>

66
00:12:57.185 --> 00:13:05.985
<v Shelly>...Mm.....A team...is bigger than a bear.....And bigger...than my math.....The morning...was on the team's side.</v>

67
00:13:06.335 --> 00:13:10.135
<v Splish>[excited]...It takes...TWO of you.....Or MORE....To lift...a LOG.</v>

68
00:13:10.485 --> 00:13:18.085
<v Splash>AND ALSO — !...With FRIENDS,...the HEAVY thing....gets LIGHTER.....The math...is just...like that.</v>

69
00:13:18.435 --> 00:13:29.235
<v Splosh>...And the BEST part....is that you DON'T...have to do it...by yourself....Like a BELL....On a COLD ROCK....BUT...with FRIENDS.</v>

70
00:13:29.585 --> 00:13:35.985
<v Old Timber>Mm.....That's itThat's it...exactly.</v>

71
00:13:36.335 --> 00:13:46.135
<v Old Timber>Now, before you go —...Splosh,...Splash,...and Splish — they have, of course, something they very much want to tell you....About the BRIDGE....The dear chaotic creatures.</v>

72
00:13:46.485 --> 00:13:55.885
<v Splosh>Mudpuppies....Mudpuppies....TODAY...on MUDPUPPY MINUTES....we will EXPLAIN....how a BRIDGE...works.</v>

73
00:13:56.235 --> 00:14:05.035
<v Splish>I have a FACT!...wait no, I have a QUESTION....A bridge...is the FLOOR...over the WET part....Isn't it?</v>

74
00:14:05.385 --> 00:14:18.185
<v Splash>AND ALSO — !...A bridge...is what you USE...when you don't want to GET wet....Bridges...were INVENTED...by — SOMEONE...who was already wet,...and DIDN'T want to do it AGAIN.</v>

75
00:14:18.535 --> 00:14:31.735
<v Splosh>...A bridge....FRIENDS....A bridge,...if you think about it,...is JUST...a long flat thing....that goes from ONE place...to ANOTHER place....Without TOUCHING the in-between part....It is...the WALK...that the LOG.....refused to BE.</v>

76
00:14:32.085 --> 00:14:40.485
<v Splish>WAIT — wait — wait — friends — IF the bridge is a flat thing...and the LOG is a flat thing....IS the LOG...also a BRIDGE?</v>

77
00:14:40.835 --> 00:14:52.235
<v Splash>AND ALSO — !...The LOG...was on the BRIDGE....SO the LOG...was a SECOND BRIDGE....on TOP of the FIRST bridge....WHICH MEANS...the friends...crossed TWO bridges...this morning....TWO.</v>

78
00:14:52.585 --> 00:15:07.985
<v Splosh>...Mudpuppies....Mudpuppies....we have SOLVED IT.....A BRIDGE means...a flat thing....that takes you somewhere....And a LOG...is a flat thing....that takes you somewhere....IF you can lift it.....Which you can....IF there are six.</v>

79
00:15:08.335 --> 00:15:21.135
<v Old Timber>...Mm.....Well....The dear chaotic creatures....They got there, in their way.....A log is a flat thing that takes you somewhere — if there are six.....That's actually...rather fine....I'll take it.</v>

80
00:15:21.485 --> 00:15:24.170
<v Bongo>Old Timber —...what did we learn today?</v>

81
00:15:24.520 --> 00:15:31.720
<v Old Timber>Mm....When Bongo asked the friends what they needed...instead of lifting alone...that's where the morning turned.</v>

82
00:15:32.070 --> 00:15:51.870
<v Old Timber>And there's a line from the Bible, my friends....From a small book by an old king named Solomon,...a long, long time ago.....The book is called Ecclesiastes....And the line is from chapter four, verse nine....The line says —...Two are better than one;...because they have a good reward for their labour.</v>

83
00:15:52.220 --> 00:16:00.100
<v Bongo>[excited]...Old Timber?...What does that LOOK like?...In an actual day?...For somebody who is listening right now?</v>

84
00:16:00.450 --> 00:16:22.250
<v Old Timber>Mm....Well, friend,...this week,...if you have a thing that feels TOO BIG —...the laundry pile,...the homework page,...the room nobody wants to clean —...try asking ONE other person...to do it WITH you.....Just one.....Say the words out loud....Can you do this with me?.....And then see what God does...with two.</v>

85
00:16:22.600 --> 00:16:29.200
<v Old Timber>Until the next breeze brings us togetherAsk kindly out there, little ones.</v>

86
00:16:29.550 --> 00:16:33.460
<v Ranger Ray>See you next time... somewhere in Shiloh Creek.</v>
